  "name": "RPlog_Corellian_Craziness_Aftermath",
  "title": "Corellian Craziness: Aftermath",
  "summary": "Patched up after the spaceport kidnapping chaos, the lightstaff-bearer Simon waits at the White Ghost, fending off a curious tanned stranger named Chapman and reuniting with the battered Corellian girl Mira. The Wroonian spacer Daana Roon lands nearby and, drawn by talk of Luke Skywalker, cautiously approaches the jittery group; a tense near-draw between her and the NRI agent Bazil McKenzie (posing as 'Mege Vauki') ends without bloodshed once everyone calms. Markus Lisardis arrives, opens his ship, and the trio agrees to follow Bazil's separate vessel to Coruscant to finally meet Skywalker, parting amicably with Daana. Aboard the White Ghost, Simon and Markus share quiet talk of lost loves and Markus's late wife Almeda during the hyperspace journey. Arriving over the overwhelming city-world of Coruscant, the nature-bred Simon recoils at the endless metal, and Bazil offers the group lodging, even a serene monk's mountain retreat, as they settle in to await their long-sought audience with the Jedi Master.",
